This isn't exclusively a Porsche innovation.  My '72 Datsun 510 had the
key on the left as well.  Never tried a LeMans start, though!

I, too, prefer a dash-mounted switch.  Making the key do two jobs on the
steering column invites rapid wear in the early column locks.
